Missing Values Alert

Indicates that a variable is missing a high percentage of values, which can lower the quality of your insights or model.

Actions to Consider
For numeric variables, consider imputing missing values by configuring statistical imputation on a numeric variable. To learn more, see Replace Missing Numerical Values.
Add the missing values in data prep and refresh your training data.
Add the missing values in the source system and refresh your training data.

Detection Methodology

Einstein Discovery raises this data alert for a variable when a threshold percentage of the values are unspecified.
title: Missing Values Alert in Salesforce Einstein Discovery
